    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-08-23T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-08-23T12:00:00-05:00" n="642"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d642">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">823.00 Revolutions/4: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-08-23T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >August 23, 1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 3:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>144. My telegram number 143 August 22, 11 p.m. Government newspaper <hi
                        rend="italic">Prensa</hi> publishes account of insurrection at Arequipa from
                        <pb facs="0815" n="721" xml:id="pg_721"/> which apparently entire garrison
                    has joined revolt, rest of country described as quiet. The President has issued
                    a decree closing until further notice the port of Mollendo to all merchant
                    vessels, national or foreign, and closing likewise the city of Arequipa and its
                    suburbs for commercial air traffic.</p>
                <p>Revolutionists have taken Mollendo. The Government has despatched one plane to
                    Arequipa and one to Mollendo to distribute literature and general purpose of
                    intimidation without actually dropping bombs or the like. The Government has
                    also sent submarine to Mollendo to blockade the port and keep closed in
                    accordance with decree described above. All quiet locally.</p>
                <p>Military and Commercial Attachés request repeat also to respective
                    departments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
